						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 6) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I, [955 A.D.]</p>						

						<p>This record refers to the 48th year of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Maduragoṇḍakō-Parakēsari</hi> and states that while Śīvarayya was administering Pulināḍu, Polleya lost his life in a raid (?) at Eḍe-ūr. The <hi rend="italic">gāvuṇḍas</hi> of the place appear to have made a gift of land-in his memory.</p>						

						</summary>
